Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "istraga":

1. Pokrenuta je *istraga* protiv sumnjivog biznismena. (An investigation has been launched against a suspicious businessman.)
2. Našli su ključne dokaze tokom *istrage*. (They found key evidence during the investigation.)
3. Advokat je podneo zahtev za obustavu *istrage*. (The lawyer filed a request for the investigation to be suspended.)
4. Policija je sprovela temeljnu *istragu* nakon pljačke. (The police conducted a thorough investigation after the robbery.)
5. Tužilac je odlučio da zatvori *istragu* zbog nedostatka dokaza. (The prosecutor decided to close the investigation due to lack of evidence.)
6. Mediji su izvestili o napretku u *istraži* ubistva. (The media reported on progress in the investigation of the murder.)
7. Osumnjičeni je priveden zbog učešća u *istraži*. (The suspect was arrested for involvement in the investigation.)
8. *Istraga* je još uvek u toku, a policija traži osumnjičenog. (The investigation is still ongoing and the police are looking for the suspect.)

(Note: the word "istraga" is highlighted with a star (*) in each sentence.) 

I hope these examples are helpful!